LIMPOPO cops have arrested over 397 suspects during
operation Fiela II. The suspects aged between 19 and 47 years were involved in various offences ranging from murder,
possession of unlicensed firearm and stolen properties, rape and house
robberies. Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said the suspects were arrested after an
intelligence led joint operation. He said they were targeting the most crime infested areas. Some of the items seized
include nine cars, 38 cell phones, fire arms, 80 ammunition, laptops, dagga,
groceries and cash. Ngoepe said the continuing fight against any form of criminality
by the members of the South African Police Service in Limpopo is still gaining
momentum.